<p><strong>Lion Greatbow</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Greatbows" href="/Greatbows" target="">Greatbow</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Lion Greatbow</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>, and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for ranged combat enhanced with gravitational power of the Starscourge and with an added unique skill, Radahn's Rain. It allows the user to fire a flurry of arrows and let it rain onto foes within range.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Greatbow of black iron wielded by General Radahn. Decorated with a lion mane motif.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Imbued with gravitational power of the Starscourge, when used along with Radahn's Spear, it becomes a true weapon of a champion.&nbsp;</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Lion Greatbow in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Trade&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Remembrance of the Starscourge" href="/Remembrance+of+the+Starscourge" target="">Remembrance of the Starscourge</a> with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Enia" href="/Enia" target="">Enia</a> at <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Roundtable Hold" href="/Roundtable+Hold" target="">Roundtable Hold</a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Lion Greatbow Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>:<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Radahn's Rain" href="/Radahn's+Rain" target="">Radahn's Rain</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Lion Greatbow</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon grants&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Radahn's Spear" href="/Radahn's+Spear" target="">Radahn's Spear</a>s&nbsp;20% increased physical damage. This is a passive effect, so it will apply to Radhan's Spears fired from another great bow, while this weapon is held in the off-hand. So, for maximum damage, the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Golem Greatbow" href="/Golem+Greatbow">Golem Greatbow</a>, which has higher AR than this weapon, should be used in the main hand to shoot Radhan's Spears.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;1000</li> 
 <li>This <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Greatbows" href="/Greatbows" target="">Greatbow</a>&nbsp;at +10 and using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Radahn's Spear" href="/Radahn's+Spear" target="">Radahn's Spear</a>&nbsp;is actually highly effective against <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Starscourge Radahn" href="/Starscourge+Radahn">Radahn</a> himself. Even with the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring HP" href="/HP" target="">HP</a> increase given by allies, as long as they keep him in one place performing his rather slow combos and distracting him you can easily tear chunks off his health with the weapon art.</li> 
 <li>All Bows (<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Crossbows" href="/Crossbows" target="">Crossbows</a>&nbsp;excepted) only need 2/3 of their STR requirement, since they can only be used two-handed. This also means only 54 points of investment into STR are needed to meet the last soft cap at 80, since 54*1.5=81.</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Moveset &amp; Videos in&nbsp;Elden Ring for&nbsp;Lion Greatbow</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Videos for the Lion Greatbow Coming Soon</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Lion Greatbow Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></p> 
<p>This upgrade can't be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a> nor boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</p> 
