				<li id="16449952" class="cmnt-root" data="10" data-d="1646391967000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578997/Lion-Greatbow" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">04 Mar 2022 06:06</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16449952" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Hey guys, if you want to take the easy route for Radahn as a melee, you will need barricade ash of war and a great shield. If you can use a bleed weapon as well you will have an easy time. Only have a couple moves you cannot fully block and barricade greatly reduces stam cost of blocking as does the great shield apparently. Regular shields will not work at an appropriate level. After failing multiple times solo and trying summons which take forever here, Using a great shield was the game changer, as well as knowing when to use torrent, which is any time hes not trying to fight melee, aside from the gravity orbs which are easier to dodge on foot.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16449952" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16449952" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>12</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-